By Wednesday night, the National Hurricane Center downgraded it to a Category 4 and to a Category 3 by Thursday morning. On Wednesday, Gilbert was classified as a Category 5 storm, the strongest and deadliest type of hurricane. He estimated damage at $8 billion. The hurricane center said Gilbert at one point was the most intense storm on record in terms of barometric pressure, which was measured Tuesday at 26. 8 north, longitude 94. The death toll from the storm's onslaught through the Caribbean islands and the Yucatan was at least 47, and damage estimates reached $8 billion. 